race.comment: Most of these on debut so betting and yard analysis could be key. GUEST HOUSE (3) has been the subject of plenty of pre-debut hype, coming clear to win a recent jump out here in good style. He's a Home Affairs colt who looks ready to run a big race. KISS ME IN PARIS (9) looks a sharp filly by Capitalist on debut for the Mark Walker yard. She cruised through her gears to win a jump out here and looks to have good early speed. UNIT FIVE (8) is a Supido colt who has been jumping out well for the Maher yard. He can land in a good spot and take beating. INVINCIBLE SON (4) is a Farnan colt for the Griffiths yard who has jumped out quite well and has claims. OMAN (10) has race experience off an even debut here and can improve.
